<HEADLINE>
<P>
GASOLINE TAX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have always found the Reagan and Bush administrations' inability to logically 
distinguish between a tax and a user fee to be hilarious, in a sad and cynical 
sort of way. Apparently, if a Democrat wants to raise revenues, it's a tax. If 
a Republican wants to raise revenues, it's a user fee. 
</P>
<P>
BRYAN D. LE BLANC 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
