<HEADLINE>
<P>
BONE MARROW DONOR BABY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This was a very private choice. It is, therefore, very disturbing to hear 
bioethicists criticize that decision and those parents on suspiciously 
unbecoming grounds. 
</P>
<P>
If it is wrong to have more than one child or a large family in order to 
protect the family unit, civilization has had it wrong since man moved off of 
the savannah and into caves. For billions of people throughout the world and 
for a million years before there was a lady bountiful or a welfare state, 
having many children was, and remains today, social security and child support 
and Meals on Wheels all rolled into one. If one child has to go to work in 
order that the family may eat and pay the rent or even so that siblings may go 
to school, is it any concern of professional do-gooders? 
</P>
<P>
ARTHUR D. SILK MD 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 
</P>
</TEXT>
