<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. EARNINGS: LOSS OF $3.7-MILLION REPORTED FOR 1989 BY BRISTOL RESEARCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bristol Research Corp., a Costa Mesa-based computer products company, reported 
a loss of $3.7 million for 1989, contrasted with a loss of about $500,000 in 
1988. Sales dropped to $3 million from $7.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
The company said the declines resulted from substantial price erosion on the 
company's commercial IBM AT-compatible products, product returns caused by 
defective components supplied by a third party, and the write-off of obsolete 
inventory. 
</P>
