<P>
Senate to Screen War Documentary: A shortened version of "Weapons of the 
Spirit," Pierre Sauvage's acclaimed documentary about a village in France that 
saved 5,000 Jews from the Nazis, will be screened at the U.S. Senate on April 
24 to commemorate Holocaust Remembrance Day. Sauvage, who was born and 
sheltered in the wartime sanctuary of Le Chambon, France, will address the 
Senate after the screening. The showing will mark the premiere of the 38-minute 
version of the 90-minute film, which will be distributed by the Anti-Defamation 
League of B'nai B'rith. GREG BRAXTON 
