<P>
2 YOUTHS ARRESTED IN DRIVE-BY SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two youths believed to be involved in a gang-related drive-by shooting have 
been arrested, Oxnard police said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The two youths, ages 15 and 17, shouted gang slogans as they pulled up beside a 
car carrying four boys at Saviers Road and Channel Islands Boulevard in Oxnard, 
said Sgt. Gary Amar of the Oxnard Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
The four boys fled in their car as the two youths chased them, Amar said. 
</P>
<P>
The passenger in the youths' car pointed a shotgun at the four boys and fired 
once into the door on the driver's side of their car, Amar said. No one was 
injured, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The four victims contacted police, who stopped the shooting suspects' vehicle 
shortly afterward and arrested the two youths, he said. 
</P>
