<HEADLINE>
<P>
EL CAMINO GUARD SIGNS WITH AIR FORCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
El Camino High guard Travis Gilley signed a letter of intent Monday to play 
basketball for the Air Force Academy. 
</P>
<P>
Gilley, a 6-foot-3 off guard, averaged 23 points, six assists and four rebounds 
for the Section 2-A champions. He also made 89 three pointers, shot 50% from 
the field and 86% from the free throw line. Included in that 86% was a 31 for 
31 streak during the Section playoffs and Southern California Regional 
Playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
Named to Cal-Hi Magazine's all-scholastic team, Gilley carried a 3.8 
grade-point average. He chose to attend Air Force over Colorado State and the 
University of Pennsylvania. 
</P>
