<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: NO FELONY CHARGES FOR OPERATION RESCUE 
LEADERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No felony conspiracy charges will be filed against two Operation Rescue leaders 
and two other anti-abortion activists who were among 246 people arrested 
Saturday during a demonstration outside a Mid-Wilshire family planning clinic, 
prosecutors said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Instead, the cases were referred to city prosecutors for the possible filing of 
misdemeanor trespassing charges, said Sandi Gibbons, a spokeswoman for the 
district attorney. 
</P>
<P>
Gibbons said there was insufficient evidence to file felony conspiracy charges 
against Joseph Foreman and Jeff White, two regional leaders of the group, and 
David Douglass and William Lundy. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Qualls of the city attorney's office was unable to immediately say whether 
charges yet been filed against any of the arrestees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
