<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
University of Arizona police have cited two Wildcat basketball players on 
unrelated misdemeanor charges, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Freshman N. Deron Johnson, 19, was cited on two misdemeanor counts of assault 
and released after female students told campus police Johnson struck them in 
the face. Johnson told authorities he did not hit either woman but that he had 
argued with one. 
</P>
<P>
Senior Harvey Mason, 21, was cited for allegedly threatening and intimidating a 
university parking and transportation officer during an exchange involving the 
ticketing and disabling of another Arizona player's car. 
</P>
