<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: PINKERTON'S RIVAL SUES OVER PERSONALITY TEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pinkerton's Inc., a large security guard company based in Van Nuys, said it was 
sued by rival Guardsmark Inc., which alleged that Pinkerton's engaged in unfair 
and deceptive trade practices. 
</P>
<P>
The suit reportedly stems from Pinkerton's use of a "personality assessment" 
test used to screen security guards. Guardsmark, a security services concern 
based in Memphis, Tenn., claimed it has licensed the test from the University 
of Minnesota and that Pinkerton's is not licensed. 
</P>
<P>
Guardsmark's suit seeks to stop Pinkerton's from using the test or advertising 
its testing program. 
</P>
<P>
"We believe this lawsuit to be entirely without merit," Gerard S. Brown, 
Pinkerton's executive vice president and general counsel, said in a statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
