<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: MICROPOLIS REPORTS LOSS OF $1.1 MILLION FOR QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Micropolis Corp., a Chatsworth maker of computer data-storage equipment, said 
it lost $1.1 million in the first quarter, compared with a $13.3-million loss a 
year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The latest loss came on a 6% drop in Micropolis' revenue -- to $75.9 million 
from $80.6 million -- in the quarter ended March 30. 
</P>
<P>
The company blamed the loss on a shortage of circuit boards used in producing 
its disk drives. Micropolis said orders for its products, however, were running 
about 10% ahead of a year earlier. 
</P>
