<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEAPING COW SQUASHES TURKISH OFFICIAL'S CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANKARA, Turkey 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A cow destined for a Turkish slaughterhouse leaped from a truck onto the roof 
of a car carrying a provincial governor, crushing it and injuring the 
occupants, the daily Gunaydin said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Erol Cakir, governor of the western Mugla province, and his wife, driver and 
security guard suffered only slight injuries, but the car was almost a total 
loss, the newspaper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
