<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOTICE TO READERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Readers of the The Times' financial tables will now find it easier to monitor 
the activity of individual stocks. 
</P>
<P>
Starting today, boldfaced lines in the listings for the New York Stock 
Exchange, American Stock Exchange and NASDAQ National Market System issues will 
indicate price changes of 5% or more from the previous day's close. Boldfaced 
lines in the weekly quotes that appear in Sunday's Business section will 
indicate a 10% or greater price change. Arrows (/) in the left margin will 
replace the footnote (u/d) to indicate a new 52-week high or low reached during 
that day's trading. 
</P>
</TEXT>
