<HEADLINE>
<P>
BHUTTO IN MECCA FOR TALKS WITH KING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JIDDA, Saudi Arabia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pakistani Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto arrived Monday on a three-day visit to 
Mecca. 
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources said she will discuss a variety of issues with King Fahd, 
including unrest in the Indian state of Kashmir. 
</P>
<P>
Bhutto, the only female head of state in the Muslim world, was accompanied by a 
45-member entourage, including her husband, Asif Ali Zardari, senior Cabinet 
ministers and high-ranking military officials. 
