<P>
MAN DIES IN OC FREEWAY CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 34-year-old Torrance man died today after his car rammed into a 
tractor-trailer on the Riverside Freeway here in Buena Park, the California 
Highway Patrol said this morning. 
</P>
<P>
Daniel M. Chang was pronounced dead on the scene shortly after the 2 a.m. 
incident in the eastbound lanes just west of the Knott Avenue exit. 
</P>
<P>
CHP Officer Angel Johnson said Chang was driving "at a high rate of speed" and 
had started to change lanes when he rear-ended the tractor-trailer. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson said both the driver of the tractor-trailer and his passenger 
complained of minor back pain but did not require hospitalization. 
