NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
BILLY IDOL FACES 5TH LEG SURGERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rock singer Billy Idol will undergo another surgery this week on a leg injured 
in a motorcycle crash, his publicist said today. 
</P>
<P>
Idol, 34, will enter Cedars-Sinai Medical Center on Wednesday for what will be 
the fifth operation on his right leg, spokeswoman Ellen Golden said. 
</P>
<P>
"They're going to insert a steel rod in his right leg, which has not been 
healing properly," she said. 
</P>
<P>
The rock star broke the leg and an arm Feb. 6 when he went through a stop sign 
on a Hollywood street and hit a car. He was heading home after completing work 
on a new album, "Charmed Life." 
</P>
</TEXT>
