<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
1ST MRS. CARSON SUES FOR MORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Johnny Carson's first wife says she can't survive on the $13,500 he pays her 
annually and is suing for more, her attorney said. 
</P>
<P>
Joan (Jody) Carson, Carson's wife of 14 years and the mother of his three sons, 
is asking him for $120,000 a year, said celebrated matrimonial lawyer Raoul 
Felder. 
</P>
<P>
Jody Carson, who told her story on the syndicated television show, "A Current 
Affair," Monday night, said she has been forced to move around and even stayed 
with her mother in a nursing home for several months last year. 
</P>
<P>
"I am in a small apartment in New York, living off the little I've saved," Jody 
Carson, 63, told columnist Cindy Adams in today's New York Post. "I've had lots 
of illness. Not just physical. I've been in a mental-health facility for panic 
disorders." 
</P>
<P>
Since his marriage to her in 1949, Carson has divorced and remarried three 
times. Carson reportedly earns $40 million a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
