<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
COLEMAN NAMED CW CAGE COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ELLENSBURG, Wash. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gil Coleman was named the new basketball coach at Central Washington University 
today, even as former coach Dean Nicholson clouded the waters with reports that 
he may rescind his resignation. 
</P>
<P>
Coleman, 33, signed a one-year contract and is the first non-Nicholson to lead 
the NAIA school's basketball program since 1929. 
</P>
<P>
Leo Nicholson was named coach that year and his son, Dean, succeeded him in 
1965. 
</P>
<P>
To satisfy affirmative action guidelines, Coleman, an assistant coach under 
Nicholson last season, will have to reapply for the position next December when 
the school begins a nationwide search for a permanent coach, Frederick said. 
</P>
<P>
The school's announcement made no mention of reports that Nicholson plans to 
take back the resignation he offered April 2, after a university auditor found 
that he improperly distributed more than $65,000 of his basketball camp 
revenues to 49 players over the last three years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
