<P>
UTAH JAZZ TICKETS SELL OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SALT LAKE CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Utah Jazz fans, queued up in a 100-yard-long line around the Salt Palace, took 
only 61 minutes to buy the 1,000 available tickets for the first round of the 
NBA playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
"With the exception of 100 tickets which remain on hold for the NBA, every seat 
in the Salt Palace was sold in record time," Jazz Marketing Vice President Jay 
Francis said. 
</P>
<P>
A record 98% of Jazz season ticket-holders bought playoff tickets, limiting the 
general public sale Monday to 1,000 tickets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
